&gt; --- In archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com, Gordon Mohr &lt;gojomo@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;&gt; shichuanwuhan@... wrote:
&gt;&gt;&gt; Hi all,
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;   Suppose I plan to crawl all professors&#39; homepages on the site: http://www.cs.umn.edu/people/faculty/index.php 
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;    To avoid redundant crawling, I set max-hop to 2 and max-path-segment to 15. However, I can only successfully crawl no more than 5 homepages(in the form of &#39;/~name/&#39;) according to crawl log. Could anyone tell me why?
&gt;&gt; Which 5 do you get?
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; What&#39;s an example of one that you think you should have gotten, but didn&#39;t?
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; Note that a crawl with the default profile, starting with just the seed 
&gt;&gt; URI &#39;http://www.cs.umn.edu/people/faculty/index.php&#39; will only visit 
&gt;&gt; outlink navigational URIs that begin 
&gt;&gt; &#39;http://www.cs.umn.edu/people/faculty/&#39;. (Those are the only URIs 
&gt;&gt; &#39;implied&#39; as in-scope by the seed. To get more, you&#39;d have to add more 
&gt;&gt; seeds or SURT-prefix scope-directives.)
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; It will not visit pages on &#39;www-users.cs.umn.edu&#39;, or even URIs on 
&gt;&gt; &#39;www.cs.umn.edu&#39; whose path-segment does not begin &#39;/people/faculty/&#39;.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; - Gordon @ IA
